Upon completion of this course, students will be expected to:
1. obtain an overview of current issues in developmental psychology;
2. understand different topics in developmental psychology and acquire preliminary literature with which to start research on a chosen
topic if interested;
3. appreciate lifespan development from an inclusive and balanced perspective attending to its bio-psycho-social aspects;
4. present a mini literature review and generate a mini grant proposal on self-chosen topics in developmental psychology.

